'''China–Guinea relations''' refer to the [[bilateralism|bilateral relations]] between [[Chinese diplomacy|China]] and [[Guinea]]. China and Guinea established [[diplomatic relations]] on October 14, 1959.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.china.org.cn/english/features/focac/183525.htm|title=Guinea-China|last=|first=|date=|website=www.china.org.cn|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref>

==Chinese development finance to Guinea==
From 2000 to 2011, there were approximately 31 Chinese official development finance projects identified in Guinea through various [[Broadcast media|media]] reports.<ref>Austin Strange, Bradley C. Parks, Michael J. Tierney, Andreas Fuchs, Axel Dreher, and Vijaya Ramachandran. 2013. China’s Development Finance to Africa: A Media-Based Approach to Data Collection. CGD Working Paper 323. Washington DC: Center for Global Development.http://china.aiddata.org{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> These projects range from the construction of a 150-bed [[hospital]] at Kipe in 2008,<ref>Strange, Parks, Tierney, Fuchs, Dreher, and Ramachandran, China’s Development Finance to Africa: A Media-Based Approach to Data Collection.http://aiddatachina.org/projects/2368</ref> to an aid package worth $5.2 million USD in 2007.<ref>Strange, Parks, Tierney, Fuchs, Dreher, and Ramachandran, China’s Development Finance to Africa: A Media-Based Approach to Data Collection.http://aiddatachina.org/projects/2360</ref>

