{{Main|Medieval Scandinavian laws}}
'''''Gutalagen''''' is an early [[Sweden|Swedish]] (or Gutnish) law book from [[Gotland]] that officially was in use until 1595, but in practice until 1645. The law book originated in about 1220 and, apart from laws, it also contains the [[Gutasaga]].

