{{multiple issues| {{cleanup-reorganize|date=October 2013}} {{unreferenced|date=October 2013}} }} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Netherlands}} "Heel de wereld" | image = [[File:Eurovision Song Contest 1958 - Corry Brokken.png|260px]] | caption = | year = 1958 | country = Netherlands | artist = [[Corry Brokken]] | as = | with = | language = Dutch | languages = | composer = Benny Vreden | lyricist = Benny Vreden | conductor = [[Dolf van der Linden]] | place = 9th | points = 1 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1958nl from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Net als toen | prev_link = Net als toen | next = Een beetje | next_link = Een beetje }} '''"Heel de wereld"''' ("The Whole World") was the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1958]], performed in [[Dutch language|Dutch]] by [[Corry Brokken]]. This was Brokken's third consecutive appearance on the Eurovision stage and it would be her last as a performer.
The song is in the ''chanson'' style, popular at the early Contest. Brokken sings that she wants to tell the whole world "my secret", because she is happy. She wonders if perhaps the world is too busy to be happy, but this does not diminish her joy. Peculiarly, she never explains why she is happy. Brokken also recorded the song in French, as "Toi mon cœur, tu sais" (translated "You My Heart, You Know").
The song was performed second on the night, following [[Italy]]'s [[Domenico Modugno]] with "[[Volare (song)|Nel blu dipinto di blu]]" and preceding [[France]]'s [[André Claveau]] with "[[Dors, mon amour]]". At the close of voting, it had received 1 point, placing 9th (equal last) in a field of 10. Until Austria's zero points in 2015, it was the lowest score of a host country's entry in the history of the contest.
It was succeeded as [[Netherlands in the Eurovision Song Contest|Dutch representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1959|1959 Contest]] by [[Teddy Scholten]] with "[['n Beetje]]". Corry Brokken returned to Eurovision in 1976, but then as the host of [[Eurovision Song Contest|that year's Contest]], held in [[The Hague]].
