{{infobox country at games | NPC = ISL | NPCname = [[Iceland Deaf Sport Organization]] | games = Deaflympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 1 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = }}
'''[[Iceland]]''' competed at the [[Deaflympics]] for the first time in [[1993 Summer Deaflympics|1993]] and also bagged their first medal at the Deaflympics, which is also Iceland's only medal in Deaflympics history<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/countries.asp?country=ISL&medalists=29|title=Handball {{!}}1993 Summer Deaflympics|last=|first=|date=|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-09-12}}</ref>. Iceland also competed in the [[1997 Summer Deaflympics|1997]], [[2005 Summer Deaflympics|2005]] and [[2013 Summer Deaflympics|2013]] Deaflympic events<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/countries.asp?country=isl|title=Countries {{!}} Deaflympics|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-12}}</ref>.
Iceland is yet to compete at the Winter Deaflympics.
