{{Infobox prepared food | name = Kūčiukai | image = Kuciukai.jpg | caption = Kūčiukai, not yet soaked in the poppy seed milk | image_alt = Kūčiukai, not yet soaked in the poppy seed milk | alternate_name = šližikai | country = [[Lithuania]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Pastry]] | served = | main_ingredient = Dough, leavening agent, [[poppy seed]]s | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''''Kūčiukai''''' (also '''''šližikai''''') is a traditional [[Lithuania]]n dish served on [[Kūčios]], the traditional [[Christmas Eve]] dinner in Lithuania.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Juciūtė|first1=Ilona|title=Kūčių stalui – spalvoti, bet visiškai natūralūs kūčiukai|url=http://www.moteris.lt/virtuve/kuciu-stalui-spalvoti-bet-visiskai-naturalus-kuciukai.d?id=73261690|website=moteris.lt|accessdate=7 June 2017|language=Lithuanian|date=24 December 2016}}</ref> They are small, slightly sweet pastries made from [[yeast|leavened]] dough and [[Poppy seed#Use as food|poppy seeds]]. There are variations in sweetness, and though usually served soaked in [[Poppy milk|poppy seed milk]], they are also eaten without it.
