{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = Our Everyday Life | image = | caption = | director = [[Ines Tanović]] | producer = | writer = Ines Tanović | starring = [[Mediha Musliović]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2015|8|20|[[Sarajevo Film Festival|SFF]]|df=yes}} | runtime = 89 minutes | country = Bosnia and Herzegovina | language = Bosnian | budget = }}
'''''Our Everyday Life''''' ({{lang-bs|'''Naša svakodnevna priča'''}}) is a 2015 Bosnian [[drama film]] directed by [[Ines Tanović]].<ref name="Sarajevo">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmneweurope.com/news/item/111082-fne-at-sarajevo-film-festival-ines-tanovic-develops-the-son |title=FNE at Sarajevo Film Festival: Ines Tanović Develops The Son |accessdate=20 August 2015 |work=Film New Europe}}</ref> It was selected as the Bosnian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[88th Academy Awards]] but it was not nominated.<ref name="Bosnia">{{cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/awards/oscars/our-everyday-life-enters-oscar-race-for-bosnia/5091883.article |title='Our Everyday Life' enters Oscar race for Bosnia |last=Petkovic |first=Vladan |work=Screendaily |date=20 August 2015 |accessdate=20 August 2015}}</ref><ref name="HWR">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bosnia-enters-everyday-life-oscar-816924 |title=Bosnia Enters 'Our Everyday Life' in Oscar Race |work=Hollywood Reporter|date=22 August 2015 |accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref>
