{{Infobox company | name = SouthWest Energy Ltd | logo = | logo_caption = | image = | image_caption = | type = Private | industry = [[Oil and gas industry|Oil and gas]] | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 2005 | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Ethiopia]] | location_country = [[Addis Ababa]] | locations = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. --> | area_served = | key_people = [[Tewodros Ashenafi]], Chairman | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | footnotes = | intl = | bodystyle = }} '''SouthWest Energy Ltd''' is an Ethiopian [[Oil and gas industry|oil and gas]] exploration and production company located in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]]. The company was established in 2005 by [[Tewodros Ashenafi]].<ref name=allafrica020310> {{cite news | url = http://allafrica.com/stories/201003020724.html | title = Ethiopia: Southwest Energy Signs With Tullow Oil PLC for Ogaden Oil Exploration | first = Mikias | last = Sebsibe | newspaper = [[Addis Fortune]] | date= 2010-03-02 | publisher = [[AllAfrica.com]] | accessdate = 2014-04-18 | id = {{subscription required}}}} </ref> It is registered in [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=bloomberg090512> {{cite news | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/southwest-energy-of-Ethiopia-optimistic-on-oil-search-in-ogaden.html | title = SouthWest Energy of Ethiopia Optimistic on Oil Search in Ogaden | first = William | last = Davison | date= 2012-05-09 | agency = [[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]] | accessdate = 2014-04-18}} </ref><ref name=upstream061010> {{cite news | url = http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article1200432.ece | title = Petronas sells Ethiopian assets to SouthWest | first = Josh | last = Lewis | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | publisher = [[NHST Media Group]] | date = 2010-10-06 | accessdate = 2014-04-10 | id = {{subscription required}}}} </ref>
In December 2005, SouthWest Energy signed a [[production sharing agreement]] with the [[Ministry of Mines and Energy (Ethiopia)|Ministry of Mines and Energy of Ethiopia]] for blocks 9 and 13 in the [[Ogaden Basin]]. In August 2008 it signed for block 9A, bringing the total acreage to {{convert|29000|km2}}.<ref name=bloomberg090512/><ref name=bloomberg051212/><ref name=st070110> {{cite news | url = http://www.sudantribune.com/spip.php?article33696 | title = British oil firm to prospect oil in Ethiopia | date = 2010-01-07 | newspaper = [[Sudan Tribune]] | accessdate = 2014-04-10}} </ref> The company plans to raise $100 million via a private placement in the first quarter of 2013 to help finance a three-well drilling program in the Ogaden Basin.<ref name=bloomberg051212> {{cite news | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-05/southwest-energy-of-ethiopia-to-raise-100-million-in-equity.html | title = SouthWest Energy of Ethiopia to Raise $100 Million in Equity | first = Sarah | last = McGregor | date = 2012-12-05 | agency = [[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]] | accessdate = 2014-04-10}} </ref> In addition, the company owns acreages at the Gambella and Jijiga basins.<ref name=ethiopia> {{cite press release | url = http://allafrica.com/stories/201304100341.html | title = Ethiopia: Southwest Energy Releases a Report On Its Oil Prospects | publisher= Government of Ethiopia | date = 2013-04-09 | accessdate = 2014-04-10}} </ref><ref name=epmag> {{cite news | url = http://www.epmag.com/Exploration/SouthWest-Energy-Aims-Oil-Ethiopia_115169 | title = SouthWest Energy Aims For Oil In Ethiopia | first = Velda | last = Addison | date = 2013-04-16 | newspaper = E&P magazine | publisher = [[Hart Energy]] | accessdate = 2014-04-18}} </ref>
